The article announces two nominations for key positions in the US government. Barry Myers of Pennsylvania is nominated to serve as the Under Secretary for Oceans and Atmosphere in the Department of Commerce. Myers is the CEO of AccuWeather and has extensive experience in weather information. He has given speeches at various organizations and has a background in business. John C. Rood of Arizona is nominated to serve as the Under Secretary of Defense for Policy. Rood has previously worked in the defense industry and has held several positions in the Federal Government, including Acting Under Secretary of State for Arms Control and International Security. He has also served at the National Security Council and the Defense Department.